front.p:
This digital edition presents the reconstruction of the capitula of series Λ(c) (according to the classification adopted in the Benedictine edition of the Vulgate; de Bruyne's repertory does not include it) that precede the Book of Iosue in the so-called Tours' Octateuch (Tours, BM, 10).
This series is generally close to de Bruyne's A series (p. 42; edited from Tours Bibles here), with which most of the capitula coincide without variation (see, e.g., cap. 7-22). By contrast with the A series, Tu's one occasionally has some more details (cap. 2, 3, 6, 23, 24), and includes two further capitula at the end (34, 35). Since the capitula are generally laconic and more elaborate summaries appear only sporadically in Tu, the direction of the transformation is probably from the A series to Tu's one (which adds details in a somewhat inconsistent manner), rather than the other way round.
Throughout the text, remarkable readings – especially discrepancies against the text of the A series as transmitted by Tours Bibles (siglum Φ; here) – are marked as follows:
italic type indicates readings that are grammatically incorrect;
pink color indicates a grammatical cause for the reading;
blue color indicates an orthographic cause for the reading;
yellow color indicates a discrepancy due to the different version of the capitula followed by Tu and Φ. Note that, for technical reasons, the filter tool ("Filtri" button below the text) cannot be customized by the reader, but it is permanently active to display the features mentioned above.
The point in the text of Iosue where Tu places the chapter number corresponding to each capitulum can be accessed either by clicking on the two-page icon next to each capitulum number, or by clicking on the "Passi paralleli" thumbnail (in the right-hand panel of the "Testo di lettura" screen).
